  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nMetricsConfig.Enabled must be true to enable the prometheus /metrics endpoint. However, this setting is also the flag to enable the metrics _pusher_. This means that even if I don't have a push service running on my machine, I have to enable it to be able to get the metrics endpoint working.\r\n\r\nThis wouldn't be a big deal except that the logs get spammed with a failure message every five seconds and it's very hard to filter out.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Enable a Prometheus metrics endpoint.\r\n2. Disable `MetricsConfig.Enabled` (documented as controlling the push metrics behavior, not the entire metrics subsystem)\r\n3. Start Nethermind.\r\n4. Attempt to connect to the metrics endpoint.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nI should get back metrics as an HTTP response.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\nConnection refused, because the endpoint is not enabled, since at https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/26848dbea0db49b9e37be8dc8909a7a69ed7d758/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Init/Steps/StartMonitoring.cs#L50 `MetricsConfig.Enabled` is checked to determine whether the entire metrics subsystem should be started.\r\n",
