    "body": "> Better solution is to keep as is and set: \"PushGatewayUrl\" to empty string in the config.\r\n\r\nShould this work now? When I set it to empty string, the exposed port remains closed and the log contains:\r\n\r\n```\r\nMar 22 19:54:41 nethermind-goerli Nethermind.Runner[3891]: 2022-03-22 19:54:41.0575|Step StartMonitoring          failed after 11ms System.ArgumentNullException: Value cannot be null. (Parameter 'pushGatewayUrl')\r\nMar 22 19:54:41 nethermind-goerli Nethermind.Runner[3891]:    at Nethermind.Monitoring.MonitoringService..ctor(IMetricsUpdater metricsUpdater, IMetricsConfig metricsConfig, ILogManager logManager)\r\nMar 22 19:54:41 nethermind-goerli Nethermind.Runner[3891]:    at Nethermind.Init.Steps.StartMonitoring.Execute(CancellationToken cancellationToken)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI guess this is due to https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/master/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Monitoring/MonitoringService.cs#L53-L55\r\n\r\n(driveby: how would I set this to empty string using the env file for systemd?)",
